title: For Sale:  Custom Interarms Mark X in 30-06 w/ scope
postcontent: Custom Interarms Mark X in 30-06. I'm sure most are unfamiliar with and never heard of Mark X rifles, so I will explain. The Mark X was manufactured by the world famed Zastava plant in Yugoslavia, assembled in Manchester, England and imported by Interarms Firearms Corp of Alexandria, Virginia. These are very well made commercial Mauser rifles, similar to FN commercial Mausers but no quite on the same level. The 98 Mauser action is THE MOST RELIABLE bolt rifle action ever designed. It was designed SPECIFICALLY for combat; to be able to reliably function under the most austere conditions. It's design has been copied by even the US in its own military rifles because of its reliability (M1903 and M1917). Ever wonder why the pre 64 Winchester Model 70s are so sought after and bring in premium prices? You guessed it...because of its Mauser type action. Ever wonder what kind of bolt rifle African Professional Hunters use when hunting dangerous game? Ding, ding, ding...you're right again...Mauser action rifles. When it comes to self preservation or the "one in a lifetime" opportunity at a trophy kill, there are those who leave nothing to chance...and they use Mauser action rifles. Now on to this firearm. The bluing is immaculate (99.9%). It comes scoped, but has good ol' iron sights in case of optics failure or loss of zero in the field. The stock is beautiful with no cracks or splits and VERY minimal handling marks. You would be hard pressed to find a finer rifle at this price point. Search around and try. I guarantee you will come up empty handed. If you require more info or pics, just shoot me a message. Located in Enterprise.

The best Browning ProSteel safe door is formed from multiple layers of steel, carefully formed together to provide superior strength, pry-resistance and attack protection. Full second panel for outstanding strength. Door face is 1 5/16 inches thick.

GEAR DRIVE LOCKING SYSTEM:
This locking system uses robust cam locks and a large, multiple diversion bar system to prevent bolt or handle pressure from reaching the lock. Forces go to the cams and diversion bars, not the lock. A 300 degree rotating gear makes operation of this mechanism three times easier to turn.

MAX LOCKING BOLTS:
The rugged steel pieces that move behind the door frame to actually hold the safe door locked and closed. The MAX Locking Bolts found only on the Pro Series line of safes, have up to 12 times more surface area to engage the stout door frame, making them 4 times stronger than traditional bolts.

PRY STOP CORNER BOLTS:
Pry-Stop Corner Bolts provide better protection than other pry-defense designs. Innovative long locking bolts extend diagonally from a reinforced support at the corners of the door to protect against pry attack at the vulnerable corner areas.

REINFORCED DOOR FRAME:
The door opening of the safe, strengthened by U-shaped steel channels, is welded around the entire perimeter to create added pry and attack resistance.

180 DEGREE HEAVY DUTY HINGES
Rugged hinges are machined from solid steel bar stock for strength. The hinges allow the door to swing open 180 degrees for unhindered access to the safe interior. Hinge-side locking bolts maintain full security even if the hinges are cut off. The door is removable to simplify moving of the safe.

DPX STORAGE SYSTEM:
The patented Duo-Plus Extra Storage System is the most versatile Browning ProSteel safe interior ever. This system maximizes gun storage space by including a modular system of door mounted racks for long guns as well as pouches and pockets for pistols and other valuables. Whereas many competitors offer these features as upgrades, the DPX storage system is a standard option on the Pinnacle Series.

DPX SCOPE SAVER (patent pending):
Found exclusively on Browning ProSteel safes, this new addition aces the optics mounted on your long guns inside the space in the door. The Scope Saver protects scoped firearms from adjacent firearms and other contents in the safe, ensuring that time spent sighting-in isn’t wasted. In addition, the space that would be taken up by a scope in a traditional safe is now freed up for another firearm. While other safes will store your guns, no other safe will protect them and keep them ready for you to use like a Browning ProSteel Safe. Any way you look at it, a scoped long gun takes up the same space of two guns in your safe, except with the DPX Scope Saver. The Scope Saver takes advantage of space no other manufacturer has ever thought of using (the space in the door) to fit a scope. With the scope recessed in the door, the scoped gun takes up no more space than an un-scoped long gun. And because the Scope Saver is integrated into the DPX door panel, your scoped long guns are right at your fingertips, easy to access as soon as the door swings open.
Watch the DPX Scope Saver in Action!--
http://youtu.be/jjEu20rVEpQ

AXIS ADJUSTABLE SHELVING (patent pending):
A safe is capable of securing more than firearms. Jewelry, documents, cameras, coin collections and other valuables — plus shooting gear — can easily fit inside a safe. The trick is maximizing storage capacity to accommodate many different items of varying size. Browning ProSteel Safes have led the industry for years in terms of safe storage solutions, now we take the concept to the highest level yet with our innovative Axis Adjustable Shelving (patent pending). Unlike shelves in other safes that are either fixed in position or only offer vertical adjustment, Axis shelves can be adjusted both vertically and horizontally to accommodate nearly any size item while working around long guns. The new Axis Adjustable Shelving comes standard on new Premium Series safes. Check it out today and see how much more you can store in your Browning ProSteel safe.
Watch the Axis Shelving System in Action!--
http://youtu.be/VRCHMbMZy_k

UL SECURITY CONTAINER RATING:
The industry standard test and rating for home/personal safes. Requires minimum construction specifications and passing a laboratory attack test. Premium Browning ProSteel safes far exceed the minimum requirements for the UL Residential Security (Tool Attack) listing.

LAYERS OF INSULATION:
The most important factor in fire protection is the total thickness of the insulation in the safe. More insulation means more protection from fire. Browning ProSteel safes use ½ inch thick gypsum panels, so the number of layers multiplied by ½ inch shows the total insulation thickness in inches.

FIRE RATING:
A laboratory measurement of time and temperature (in Fahrenheit) used to compare the relative amount of fire resistance provided by a safe. A Browning ProSteel safe with a longer fire rating time provides more fire protection than a safe with a shorter time.

S&G MECHANICAL STANDARD

S&G ELECTRONIC LOCK UPGRADE AVAILABLE*
The S&G Electronic Lock is an advanced security system manufactured by the leader in the lock industry. Includes many technical security features. Standard on NRA.

SECURAM BIOMETRIC LOCK UPGRADE AVAILABLE*
The SecuRam Biometric Lock uses the uniqueness of an individual fingerprint as the combination in this advanced security solution. The lock opens with either a fingerprint or a multi-digit code. It is highly secure and operates very quickly. Simple programming instructions. LCD Screen.

UL LISTED
MADE IN THE USA

postcontent:
The VZ58 - 2008 V (Výsadkový—"airborne"), features a side-folding metal shoulder stock.
Dubbed the VZ2008, this carbine sports the side-folding steel stock and features a combination of original Czech and new US-made parts for legality.
light and compact handling characteristics of the carbine. With the stock folded, the 7-pound VZ2008 measures just over 26 inches long. This compact size, combined with the powerful 7.62x39mm chambering and 30 + 1 capacity makes it extremely well suited as a law enforcement patrol rifle.
Over the course of a few hundred rounds, the rifle performed without a hitch. Despite its light weight and compact dimensions, the perceived recoil of the 7.62x39mm carbine proved to be quite pleasant and manageable. Accuracy at 100 yards was also quite good; particularly considering the fact the rifle was tested with only the iron sights.
•	All VZ58  - 2008 rifles possess a milled receiver; the vast majority of AK-47s are stamped. 
•	Even with the milled receiver it is almost one pound lighter than a stamped AK-47.
•	The bolt of the VZ 2008 stays open after the last round in the magazine has been fired.
•	The VZ 2008 can be reloaded with stripper clips while the magazine is inserted in the rifle.
•	The safety is more ergonomic making a faster first shot possible with the VZ2008.
•	The ejection port is HUGE. There is no chance of an empty case getting stuck in the action of the VZ2008.
•	The VZ2008 gas piston can be removed or exchanged without tools.
•	The alloy magazine of the VZ2008 is half the weight of the steel AK-47 magazine.
•	The VZ2008 is striker fired unlike the hammer fired AK-47. This reduces the number of parts and possible points of failure.

•	700 rounds, no cleaning, no problems at all 
•	Battle rifle accuracy that I am sure I could improve

•	Minimal buildup after shooting

title: For Sale:  .45 ACP once fired brass
postcontent:
For Sale:
Over 1000 pieces of once fired 45 ACP brass.  All brass has been tumbled in corn cob media for 24 hours and is ready to load.  I'm basing my count off weight so here is how i got there (disclosure im not math genius)
1 piece of brass weighs 0.189 oz so well call it 0.2 oz
5 pieces of brass make 1 oz
80 pieces of brass make 1 lb
Total weight of the box is 15.8lbs so I multiplied 15.8 times 80 and get 1,264 pieces of brass.
I'm listing it at 1000 pieces in the event that there is some residual media still in there that i missed, I rounded the single case weight up and also to give someone a good deal.  Please be able to meet face to face in the Puyallup / Pierce County area.  I am willing to ship within the US via Priority Mail at the buyers expense.  Thanks for looking.
